name academicons
category Package
revision 79395
shortdesc Font containing high quality icons of online academic profiles
longdesc The academicons package provides access in (La)TeX to 146 high
longdesc quality icons of online academic profiles included in the free
longdesc "Academicons" font. This package works with both Xe(La)TeX or
longdesc Lua(La)TeX by using fontspec to load the included font, as well
longdesc as with pdf(La)TeX by loading a Type 1 converted format of the
longdesc original font. The "Academicons" font was designed by James
longdesc Walsh and released (see http://jpswalsh.github.io/academicons/)
longdesc under the open SIL Open Font License. This package is a
longdesc redistribution of the free "Academicons" font with specific
longdesc bindings for (La)TeX. It is inspired and based on the
longdesc fontawesome package. The generic \aiicon macro takes as
longdesc mandatory argument the [?]name[?] of the desired icon. Icons
longdesc can also be accessed directly by their respective macro. For
longdesc example, \aiicon{googlescholar} yields the same result as
longdesc \aiGoogleScholar. The full list of icons with their respective
longdesc names and direct commands can be found in the manual.
execute addMap academicons.map
