name bankstatement
category Package
revision 75301
shortdesc A LaTeX class for bank statements based on csv data
longdesc More and more banks allow their customers to download posting
longdesc records in various formats. By using the bankstatement class,
longdesc you can create bank statements, as long as a csv format is
longdesc available. At the moment, the csv-mt940 and csv-camt formats --
longdesc used by many german Sparkassen -- are supported. You can quite
longdesc easily add support for other csv formats. Simply define the
longdesc order of the keys in the csv data file and how to use them. The
longdesc terminology in this class -- such as BIC (Business Identifier
longdesc Code) or IBAN (International Bank Account Number) -- is based
longdesc on usage in the SEPA (Single Euro Payments Area). The user may
longdesc adjust the terminology to suit local needs.
