name beamertheme-durham
category Package
revision 78101
shortdesc A content-first Beamer theme for teaching, research, and long-form academic presentations
longdesc This package provides the Durham Beamer Theme, a content-first
longdesc presentation theme for LaTeX Beamer designed for teaching,
longdesc research, and long-form academic presentations. The theme
longdesc emphasizes structural clarity, pacing awareness, and layout
longdesc stability under dense textual and mathematical content. It is
longdesc implemented entirely from first principles and not derived from
longdesc any existing Beamer theme. Conceptual inspiration from
longdesc established themes such as Metropolis is acknowledged; no
longdesc external code is reused. The color palette is inspired by the
longdesc visual identity of Durham University. This package is an
longdesc independent academic contribution and not an official or
longdesc endorsed Durham University template. The package includes a
longdesc modular theme implementation, a demo document with compiled
longdesc PDF, and a user manual.
containersize 3892
containerchecksum c5f3fa4b273db6ad0b195ac31ac2045c3501aceb91c527784cf3671f14e211c2e206f8ba3554f8f4d94fc69b5f9b05438e07b5a7093cc0023af4fbc17c0ef2b5
