name bnumexpr
category Package
revision 77682
shortdesc Extends eTeX's \numexpr...\relax construct to big integers
longdesc The package provides the command \bnumeval, which extends
longdesc LaTeX's \inteval with support for arbitrarily big integers, //
longdesc for floored division, /: for the associated remainder, ^ and **
longdesc for powers, ! for factorials, 0b, 0o and ', 0x and ", as
longdesc prefixes for binary, octal, or hexadecimal inputs. With the
longdesc optional argument [h] (or [o] or [b]) the output is converted
longdesc to hexadecimal (or octal, or binary).
