name latex
category Package
revision 79234
shortdesc A TeX macro package that defines LaTeX
longdesc LaTeX is a widely-used macro package (format) for TeX,
longdesc providing many basic document formatting commands extended by a
longdesc wide range of packages. It was originally created by Leslie
longdesc Lamport, whose last release was LaTeX 2.09. The current LaTeX
longdesc superseded that release in June 1994. The basic distribution is
longdesc catalogued separately, at latex-base. Apart from a large set of
longdesc contributed packages and third-party documentation (elsewhere
longdesc on the archive), the distribution includes: a number of
longdesc required packages, which LaTeX authors may assume will be
longdesc present on any system running LaTeX; and a minimal set of
longdesc documentation detailing differences from the 'old' version of
longdesc LaTeX in the areas of user commands, font selection and
longdesc control, class and package writing, font encodings,
longdesc configuration options and modification of LaTeX. For
longdesc downloading details, documentation links, etc., see the linked
longdesc catalogue entries above.
